The paper deals with frequent sequence mining, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of data mining and machine learning. The paper proposes a unified framework for subsequence constraints, which is relevant to the database community (cs.DB) and the data structures and algorithms community (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithms for efficient mining of frequent subsequences, which is relevant to the machine learning community (cs.LG) and the artificial intelligence community (cs.AI). Finally, the paper includes an experimental study on real-world datasets, which is relevant to the information retrieval community (cs.IR).
